commit.message: Fix make distcheck. Was failing to have correct python paths
Remove python global exception handler since its deprecated

Updated documentation (#46)

* POSIX is written in uppercase

* Split examples into a proper markdown list and separate code-blocks

With this, it is easier to copy a specific example, we also get syntax
highlighting.

* Drop empty NEWS file, we're using ChangeLog

* Remove README, ship README.md instead

README is almost empty, the only information that is no longer
accessible is a reference to the package homepage.
